news.title: Brigade Enterprises buys additional stake of 12.50% in BCV Developers for Rs 20.21 crore
news.para: About 35,61,550 (12.50%) equity shares of BCV Developers have been acquired. Accordingly, the shareholding of Brigade Enterprises has been increased from 50.01% to 62.51% in BCV Developers.

news.title: Bank of America pays $12 million fine for misreporting mortgage data
news.para: The U.S. Consumer Financial Protection Bureau said on Tuesday that more than 400 loan officers at the second-largest U.S. bank failed to ask applicants required questions about their race, ethnicity and sex, and then falsely reported that the applicants chose not to respond.

news.title: Aliaxis appoints Arvind Chandra as new divisional CEO of Ashirvad Pipes
news.para: "India is a high-growth market for Aliaxis for the years to come and Arvind will help bring our Indian operations to the next level," said Eric Olsen, chief executive officer of Aliaxis Group.

news.title: Hiranandani Group forays into service consultant development model
news.para: Hiranandani Group has commenced work on its first project Vista spanned across 3.33 lakh sq ft at Andheri West, Mumbai. The project will be delivered in December 2028. Development service model will start with Andheri West, followed by Versova and Chembur.

news.title: Directions issued to ensure strict implementation of GRAP-I, GRAP-II restrictions in Delhi
news.para: "The ban on BS-III petrol and BS-IV diesel vehicles have been removed and restrictions on construction and demolition lifted," Rai added.

news.title: Government to make unique identifier mandatory for construction workers: Labour Secretary
news.para: This identifier, which will be linked to Aadhaar and integrated into the e-Shram database, will facilitate the portability of benefits. It doesn't matter if anyone is in Delhi today or Mumbai tomorrow, the family's entitlements should remain accessible, Labour Secretary Arti Ahuja said.

news.title: WorkEZ looks to invest Rs 63 crore over next 12 months
news.para: Work Easy Space Solutions has leased four new centres across Chennai, Bengaluru and Coimbatore. With this expansion, its managed office space portfolio now spans 1.1 million sq ft with over 22,000 workstations across 12 centres in three cities.

news.title: Bhubaneswar civic body extracts 6,500-tonne fuel for cement units from legacy waste
news.para: Between November 1 and 15, the civic body has processed 18,000 metric tonnes of waste using two trommel machines and two mobile segregators.

news.title: Unitech buyers have eyes set on SC as projects stuck for years await layout plan green light
news.para: On November 3, the top court directed the Unitech board and the Noida Authority to reach mutually agreed upon terms before finalising the layout plans.

news.title: Odisha: 100-day challenge to complete PMAY houses
news.para: In a letter to municipal commissioners and executive officers of the ULBs, additional secretary of the urban development department, Debasis Singh, said under PMAY-U, 28,472 units are under various stages of construction, which must be completed before December 2024.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP inspects 22 lifts in Sobha City after residents file plaints
news.para: Not just this, the residents have approached almost all higher authorities, including CM window, DTCP, DHBVN and others, for replacement of the lifts for safety of residents and preventing any mishap but no concrete action has been taken so far.

news.title: Landowner, developer can't block layout access: Karnataka HC
news.para: A division bench comprising Chief Justice Prasanna B Varale and Justice Krishna S Dixit made this observation while dismissing the writ appeal filed by Pabba Reddy Kodandarami Reddy, a landowner from Bellandur in Bengaluru.

news.title: Delhi RERA withdraws order banning registration of new property after meeting LG
news.para: "The LG impressed upon and requested the RERA to revisit its order in view of the hardship it is causing to common people in Delhi," said a Raj Niwas official.

news.title: Ghaziabad mayor warns of fines on townships with no waste processing plants
news.para: “We will be conducting surprise inspections in these societies to check where the builders and AOA are dumping the garbage. If they are found without a processing plant for segregation of wet and dry garbage, we will issue notice and impose a fine of up to Rs 1 lakh,” said mayor Dayal.

news.title: After tremors, Navi Mumbai builders take stock of earthquake resistance
news.para: ​A day later, builders and civic officials said housing and commercial towers, as well as other structures in Navi Mumbai are safe as the base and plinth of buildings are made earthquake-resistant at the time of construction.

news.title: Kolkata: Large realty projects to pay water infrastructure development fee
news.para: The proposal, already passed by KMC House, will be effective December 1. The levy will be imposed on all upcoming realty projects that exceed 2,000sq m (20,000sq ft) in size with the civic body charging Rs 100/ sq m (1,000 sq ft).

news.title: Court allows ED's plea for CCTV at former HDIL promoter's home
news.para: In a plea submitted by special public prosecutor Kavita Patil, the ED said he may tamper with evidence and influence witnesses and dispose of unidentified assets.

news.title: LG urges Delhi RERA to revisit order, says it stalled property registration in the city
news.para: Saxena on Tuesday met the chairman and members of Delhi RERA along with the Chief Secretary and divisional commissioner at Raj Niwas to address the issue.
